<TITLE> India's Power Finance Corp to raise 1.5 bln rupees </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MUMBAI, June 4 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India's state-run Power Finance Corp will raise at least 1.5 billion rupees through a bond sale, with the option to retain an additional unspecified greenshoe amount, a company source said on Monday. The company will sell a 3-year paper with 9.9 percent coupon, and a 5-year paper with a 10 percent coupon, both payable annually, the source said. The bonds have been rated "AAA" by Crisil and ICRA. The issue will close on June 8
